$ SQLite: indices

{ Covering indices #covering-indices

  A *covering index* is an index that contains all data for a specific → development/databases/SQLite/sql/select[select statement]. In such a case, SQLite doesn't have to visit the indexed table:
  gh|about-sqlite|/indices/covering-index.sql||

}
{ Misc

  It's not possible to create indices on → development/databases/SQLite/tables/virtual[virtual tables] in SQLite;

}
sa:
  → development/databases/SQLite/indices/indexed-by[Force using a specific index]
